@mar10, we were planning on overriding `streamData()`, but are currently not doing that. All I'm doing is overriding `processData()` to forward the `data_stream` iterator (to a an object with a `read()` method that wraps it), instead of iterating over it.

If you want to enable just this, you could allow the file-object returned by `res.beginWrite()` to have a `writeLines()` method, which if present, will be passed the `data_stream` iterator. I think this would satisfy our requirements for PUT requests.

However, we may still need the ability to override `RequestServer` methods for the other use cases that @tomviner mentioned: https://github.com/mar10/wsgidav/issues/48#issuecomment-253177004.

