Will probably be a little longer than expected. I've done some significant work on this to support on the fly enabling/disabling. This work includes support for checking the connect events and making sure only callbacks for "enabled" plugins are rendered out.

I've also changed the way events are connected (now done in the instance of the Plugin class) rather than standalone functions in the __init__.py (although for backwards compatibility this will still work). In the setup(), the developer can either call the connect_event() functions manually, or write the configure to info.json like:

    "connect_events": [
        {
            "connect_event": "after_navigation",
            "method": "some_method"
        }, 
    ]

I've tried to keep as much backwards compatibility as possible - but for what I need this thing to do, it's very likely I will be introducing breaking changes. Although, the framework this will become could be very useful for a lot of projects.

I'll pull request my changes when they are ready and you can decide if you want to build them into your plugin.

