As a side note, I was going to ditch my service caching in favor of using the ObjectCache to reduce the impact of loading the WSDL repeatedly, but it seems like the `AdWordsClient.GetService` method needs to provide `cachingpolicy=1` as a kwarg to `suds.client.Client` for the cache to work. Otherwise this bit in the `suds.reader.DefinitionReader` class will override the passed-in cache and set it to NoCache:

```
    def cache(self):
        """
        Get the cache.
        @return: The I{cache} when I{cachingpolicy} = B{1}.
        @rtype: L{Cache}
        """
        if self.options.cachingpolicy == 1:
            return self.options.cache
        return NoCache()
```

